    "Thus, the maximum-likelihood estimation (MLE) method that always yields physically sensible results is devised for the reconstruction 42, 43.",
    "By introducing the Lagrange multiplier and constructing an appropriate iteration form, MLE method preserves the positive semi-definiteness and trace normalization of the process matrix (see Supplementary Note 3).",
    "The conformity between theory and experiment is evaluated by process fidelity F ¼ Trðχ t χ e Þ, which is the trace of the product of theoretical process matrix χ t and experimental process matrix χ e.",
    "In this experiment, we achieve F 3DX1 ¼ 98:4ð2Þ%, F 3DH1 ¼ 99:4ð3Þ% and F CNOT ¼ 99:6ð2Þ%, respectively.",
    "To quantify the comparison between theoretical, simulated and experimental tomography matrices, the mean squared errors (MSEs) of them for different gates are exhibited in Fig. 3g."
  ],
